</mei>

<!--
VOICING PLAN — 4151 O Lord, I Am Not Worthy (Bb major)
Key: Bb (2 flats: Bb, Eb).

m.1: I "334" root+octave Bb1-F2-Bb2-D3, RH D4-F4 — warm entry
m.2: I→V split, smooth F2-C3-A3 for V, contrary motion
m.3: V7 full "333" with Eb in bass — dominant tension
m.4: I quartal color "44" RH sus, LH "334" — momentary openness
m.5: V→ii sequential motion, RH descends F-Bb-Am
m.6: vi (sub for A)→IV, RH thirds stepping up
m.7: I→V7 buildup to climax, full 4-note LH V7 chord
m.8: Final I all sustained, 7-note spread across all voices

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Chromatic-adjacent Eb⁴ in m.3/m.6 gives modal color typical of this tune.
- V7 root F appears as pedal in both m.3 and m.7, grounding the dominant.
- Final measures: top voice descends C5→Bb4, bass Bb1 frames the cadence.

TEXTURE ARC:
Pickup: silence in harp — melody alone enters
mm.1-2: Moderate, 2-voice RH opens, builds with V at m.2
mm.3-4: V7 richness then quartal sus — contrast
mm.5-6: Sequential harmonies, moving voices
mm.7-8: Climactic I→V7→I, full 7-voice final chord
-->
